Considering that this is a starter card, I actually really like it. I think hemokinesis is not a fair comparison, since that's an uncommon you have to specifically find and add to your deck, whereas you start off with tackle. At the beginning of a run, frontloaded damage is the name of the game, and this card deals a ton of damage for 1 energy, significantly improving your cultist and jaw wurm fights, as well as louses if you upgrade it. It's exactly the kind of card you want to deal with all 3 act 1 elites, which gives you a nice leg up in getting started on hunting them down confidently. Sure, it will fall off later in the run, and you probably won't be playing it very often in act 3 and beyond, but it's already done its job and gotten you through acts 1 and 2, and probably given you a chance to snowball in other areas like relics and souls. I think it's close between upgrading tackle and corrosive spit (split is also reasonable), this gives an impressive +4 to damage, but spit reduces to a 0 cost card, which is really valuable in the early game, but it is a skill which you may not want to play into gremlin nob, and the goop will be blocked into tri-sentries, so I often choose tackle to have the best matchup I can against the act 1 elites.

It's worth noting that the self damage really isn't much of a drawback here. You can block it, use roll through to ignore it, simply heal it with your starting relic, or use the myriad of other healing sources slime boss has access to. You can very comfortably use a defend to block the damage if tackle is all you need to end the fight, and you can also use leeching slimes to gain block at the start of your turn to cover this. You will almost never be investing in the tackle synergies, as they are just too weak to justify adding so many frontloaded damage cards to your deck, but they can be fine tools when you need them in the early game, and this card performs that job admirably.

Reporting in on the A1 slime boss forcing Just Desserts / Growth Punch:
* Had both by mid Act 2 (visiting lots of shops helps since all you need is 2 uncommons)
* Beyond Perfect in 41:54
* Only got the Punch up to 65 block/dmg before Neow was dead, since she ran out of HP
* Finished with a 11 card deck, 5 of which were some kind of Lick+ and 1 of which was Quick Snack (the other 3 were two defends and a Duplicated Form+ mostly for the energy)
